      <title>1808 Jun. 5, Port Royal, Montgomery County, Tennessee [to] John Sevier / Montgomery County, Tennessee [citizenry]</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>This is a letter from the Montgomery citizenry to Governor John Sevier, dated June 5, 1808. The citizenry is requesting that Sevier call a special session of the General Assembly to address economical problems that have occurred due to the Embargo Act of 1807. The letter points out that other states like Georgia and Virginia have already done this. The citizenry would also like to use the session to address political problems inherent in the form of government that Tennessee has undertaken.</abstract>
